-- Bulgaria May Hold Early Elections on May 12, 24 Hours Reports
-- B y   E l i z a b e t h   K o n s t a n t i n o v a
-- 2013-02-27T08:43:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-27/bulgaria-may-hold-early-elections-on-may-12-24-hours-reports.html
Bulgaria may hold a snap vote on May
12,  24 Hours  newspaper reported, citing Mihail Mihailov, a
lawmaker from the opposition Blue Coalition.  The date was proposed at the meeting of the National
Security Council convened by President Rosen Plevneliev
yesterday, according to the newspaper. The Council includes the
leaders of all political parties.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elizabeth Konstantinova in Sofia at 
 ekonstantino@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  